<node TEXT="SciPy conf open referee process&#xa;2013-08-05&#xa;Editor as bdfl&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;Cost of open access on NSF grant&#xa;&#xa;Open data not enough&#xa;Open code not enough&#xa;&#xa;Platform needs to also be open&#xa;&#xa;Translucency versus transparency&#xa;2013-08-05&#xa;This is a test&#xa;Editor as bdfl&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;Cost of open access on NSF grant&#xa;&#xa;Open data not enough&#xa;Open code not enough&#xa;&#xa;Platform needs to also be open&#xa;&#xa;Translucency versus transparency&#xa;Cost of openaccess&#xa;&#xa;6k per article&#xa;Express relative to average NSF grant&#xa;Take account of overhead&#xa;Data alone is not enough for replication. You also need the code.&#xa;&#xa;Code and data is not enough for replication, you also need a fully open platform.&#xa;&#xa;&quot;Here is my data and stata-sas-spss script&quot; isn&apos;t going to support full replication.&#xa;&#xa;Rounding issues cross platform. Not an easy problem but one more transparent on open platforms&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;Translucency versus transparency. The former is applicable in the closed platform open code and data case, while the latter is open platform, code and data.&#xa;&#xa;Goal is science. That should drive our decisions as scientists.&#xa;Editor as pull request manager, refs and authors as submitters&#xa;&#xa;&#xa;Proposal review anonymous on review side. Candor versus collaboration. Would this be different if the reviews were not anonymous.&#xa;&#xa;Small resources biases towards previous record. Novel ideas get funded less often." ID="ID_1122025299" CREATED="1378905250353" MODIFIED="1378905252694"/>
</node>
